<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 1006/98 of 14 May 1998 amending Regulation (EC) No 939/97 laying down detailed rules concerning the implementation of Council Regulation (EC) No 338/97 on the protection of species of wild fauna and flora by regulating trade therein </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr1006/98, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 939/97, millega s&auml;testatakse n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 338/97 (looduslike looma- ja taimeliikide kaitse kohta nendega kauplemise reguleerimise teel) &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad 14. mai 1998 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 338/97 of 9 December 1996 on the protection of species of wild fauna and flora by regulating trade therein (1), as last amended by Commission Regulation (EC) No 2307/97 (2), and in particular point 2 of Article 19 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 9. detsembri 1996. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 338/97 looduslike looma- ja taimeliikide kaitse kohta nendega kauplemise reguleerimise teel, (1) viimati muudetud komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2307/97, (2) eriti selle artikli 19 punkti 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 7(3) of Regulation (EC) No 338/97 provides for a derogation from Articles 4 and 5 of that Regulation for personal and household effects in compliance with provisions specified by the Commission; whereas the provisions concerned were laid down in Articles 27 and 28 of Commission Regulation (EC) No 939/97 (3), as amended by Regulation (EC) No 767/98 (4); whereas those Articles need to be amended in order to prevent abuse of their provisions; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 338/97 artikli 7 l&otilde;ikega 3 n&auml;hakse isiklike asjade ja majatarvete kohta ette komisjoni kehtestatud s&auml;tete kohased erandid nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklitest 4 ja 5; asjaomased s&auml;tted kehtestati komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 939/97 (3) (muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 767/98) (4) artiklitega 27 ja 28; neid artikleid on tarvis muuta v&auml;ltimaks nende s&auml;tete kuritarvitamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to prevent abuse, the conditions for the application of the derogation regulated by Articles 27 and 28 of Regulation (EC) No 939/97 need to be clarified by referring to the definition laid down in Article 2(j) of Regulation (EC) No 338/97, regard being had to the objectives of the latter Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> kuritarvitamise v&auml;ltimiseks on m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 939/97 artiklitega 27 ja 28 reguleeritud erandi kohaldamise tingimusi tarvis t&auml;psustada viitega m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 338/97 artikli 2 punktis j s&auml;testatud m&auml;&auml;ratlusele, pidades silmas viimati nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse eesm&auml;rke; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas goods that are introduced into and/or exported or re-exported from the Community in order to be used for commercial gain, sold, displayed for commercial purposes, kept for sale, offered for sale or transported for sale, cannot be considered to be the belongings of a private individual that form or are intended to form part of his normal goods and chattels; </inglise>
<eesti> kaupu, mida tuuakse &uuml;hendusse ja/v&otilde;i eksporditakse v&otilde;i reeksporditakse &uuml;hendusest selleks, et neid kasutada tulunduslikul eesm&auml;rgil, m&uuml;&uuml;a, n&auml;idata kaubanduslikul eesm&auml;rgil, s&auml;ilitada, pakkuda v&otilde;i transportida m&uuml;&uuml;giks, ei v&otilde;i k&auml;sitada &uuml;ksikisiku omandina, mis moodustavad v&otilde;i on m&otilde;eldud moodustama osa tema igap&auml;evastest tarbeasjadest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Committee on Trade in Wild Fauna and Flora, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las looduslike looma- ja taimeliikidega kauplemise komitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Regulation (EC) No 939/97 is hereby amended as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 939/97 j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The following text is inserted as the first subparagraph of Article 27(1): </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 27 l&otilde;ike 1 esimesele l&otilde;igule lisatakse j&auml;rgmine tekst: </eesti>
<inglise> 'For the purposes of the application of the derogation laid down in Article 7(3) of Regulation (EC) No 338/97 from Article 4 of that Regulation, goods that are introduced into the Community in order to be used for commercial gain, sold, displayed for commercial purposes, kept for sale, offered for sale or transported for sale cannot be considered to be personal or household effects. </inglise>
<eesti> "Kui kohaldatakse m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 338/97 artikli 7 l&otilde;ikega 3 etten&auml;htud erandit selle m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklist 4, ei v&otilde;i kaupu, mida tuuakse &uuml;hendusse, et neid kasutada tulunduslikul eesm&auml;rgil, m&uuml;&uuml;a, n&auml;idata kaubanduslikul eesm&auml;rgil, s&auml;ilitada, pakkuda v&otilde;i traksportida m&uuml;&uuml;giks, k&auml;sitada &uuml;ksikisiku omandina, mis moodustavad v&otilde;i on m&otilde;eldud moodustama osa tema isiklikest asjadest v&otilde;i majatarvetest." </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The following text is inserted as the first subparagraph of Article 28(1): </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 28 l&otilde;ike 1 esimesse l&otilde;ikesse lisatakse esimene l&otilde;ik j&auml;rgmises s&otilde;nastuses: </eesti>
<inglise> 'For the purposes of the application of the derogation laid down in Article 7(3) of Regulation (EC) No 338/97 from Article 5 of that Regulation, goods that are exported or re-exported from the Community in order to be used for commercial gain, sold, displayed for commercial purposes, kept for sale, offered for sale or transported for sale cannot be considered to be personal or household effects. </inglise>
<eesti> "Kui kohaldatakse m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 338/97 artikli 7 l&otilde;ikega 3 etten&auml;htud erandit selle m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklist 5, ei v&otilde;i kaupu, mida eksporditakse v&otilde;i reeksporditakse &uuml;hendusest, selleks et neid kasutada tulunduslikul eesm&auml;rgil, m&uuml;&uuml;a, n&auml;idata kaubanduslikul eesm&auml;rgil, s&auml;ilitada, pakkuda v&otilde;i transportida m&uuml;&uuml;giks, k&auml;sitada &uuml;ksikisiku omandina, mis moodustavad v&otilde;i on m&otilde;eldud moodustama osa tema isiklikest asjadest v&otilde;i majatarvetest." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following that of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 14 May 1998. </inglise>
